Alrighty.

* Diana panted as she ran behind Rion, not even looking over her fur covered 
shoulder to see if that monster with teeth was following them.
She was only seconds behind Rion and she nearly tripped over plant roots as 
she hit the vegetation of the small grove with a smack.
The plants were so thick that it was very hard to see where she was going 
and without warning she saw Rion's back suddenly.
She let out a yell as she put on the breaks, though it was too late.  She's 
hit him head on!
Plus...Rion had mannaged to stop at the edge of a sandy cliff that sloped 
down into the planes, and the distant gray patch could only be a limp of 
twisted metal.
The Cybertronain Fire.*
